The paper deals with the problem of testing whether two distributions are approximately equal, given a sequence of independent samples from an unknown distribution. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and statistics (cs.SI). However, since the focus of the paper is on designing an efficient algorithm for the problem, we can expect that the most likely categories are those that deal with algorithm design and analysis, such as cs.DS, cs.IT, and cs.CC. The categories of cs.LG and cs.SI are also relevant, but they may be less likely since they are more focused on the statistical aspects of the problem.
